 charities. When discussing social policy, charities have a real expertise about the issues on \nwhich they work and want to share this information", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 482, "end_char_idx": 1136, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "[Excerpt from document]\n{metadata_str}\nExcerpt:\n-----\n{content}\n-----\n", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "cc4ac948-9afc-4ce3-89dd-98eecc4a9c75": {"__data__": {"id_": "cc4ac948-9afc-4ce3-89dd-98eecc4a9c75", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"page_label": "1", "file_name": "Political-Activities-Aug-2018.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\Political-Activities-Aug-2018.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 147985, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16", "prev_section_summary": "The section discusses the general rule regarding charities and political activities, non-partisan political activities, and advocacy activities that are not considered political activities. It also mentions COCo receiving requests for information about the legal limitations on political activities by registered charities, highlighting the expertise charities have on social policy issues they work on.", "next_section_summary": "The section discusses the rules and guidelines surrounding political activities for charities, including what is considered a political activity, what activities are allowed, and the limitations on these activities. It also mentions the importance of charities sharing their expertise on social issues with government bodies and the public. The section references criticisms of the political activity rules, updates on CRA's political activities audit of charities, and recent government consultations on the rules. The information provided is based on the CRA's policy statement on political activities.", "section_summary": "The section discusses the legal limitations on political activities for registered charities, including what constitutes a political activity, what types are allowed, and how many can be organized or participated in each year. It also addresses the importance of understanding these rules for organizations considering applying for charitable status. The key topics include the expertise of charities in social policy, sharing knowledge with government bodies and the public, and the implications for maintaining charitable status. The entities involved are registered charities, government bodies, and organizations considering charitable status.", "questions_this_excerpt_can_answer": "1. What are the legal limitations on political activities for registered charities, including what constitutes a political activity, what types are allowed, and how many can be organized or participated in each year?\n2. How do charities share their expertise on social policy issues with government bodies and the general public while maintaining their charitable status?\n3. What are the rules and guidelines surrounding political activities for charities, and what are the criticisms of these rules as mentioned in the document?"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "1c866f43-d20d-4c23-a515-c2655d09daf9", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"page_label": "1", "file_name": "Political-Activities-Aug-2018.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\Political-Activities-Aug-2018.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 147985, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "6cf1ca7f40f4778f435ccba0701f85e37ba14033fad1b50f8b4c45f6463c3e93", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "f6b326c6-b56c-493e-80e4-2bee45e54eeb", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {"page_label": "1", "file_name": "Political-Activities-Aug-2018.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\Political-Activities-Aug-2018.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 147985, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "c3e799c1201205645f711da11655e72f992b83f299561df5c12219cf02f0024a", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "3": {"node_id": "52f5435f-632c-45be-ad5b-8a4929d5029b", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "48538ec9cc28aab280da1a229a4c3d93249d7c76b5b3e9eddda29dc2da2030b2", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "\u2026   \u2026   \u2026   \u2026   \u2026   \u2026   \u2026   \u2026   \u2026   \u2026   \u2026   \u2026   .\n5  The advocacy activities that are not considered political activities \u2026   \u2026   \u2026   \u2026   \u2026   \u2026   \u2026   ..\n1\n2\n3\n4\n7\nAt COCo, we often receive requests for information about the legal limitations on political activities undertaken \nby registered charities. When discussing social policy, charities have a real expertise about the issues on \nwhich they work and want to share this information with government bodies and the general public. \nIn order to share their knowledge and experience without losing their charitable status, charities want to \nknow \nwhat is considered a political activity, what kind of political activities are allowed, and how \nmany of these activities they can organize or participate in each year. Organizations that are considering \napplying for charitable status also want to understand the rules about political activities so they can decide \nif registering as a charity is right for their organization.\nThis info-sheet provides an introduction to the", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 699, "end_char_idx": 1724, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "[Excerpt from document]\n{metadata_str}\nExcerpt:\n-----\n{content}\n-----\n", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "52f5435f-632c-45be-ad5b-8a4929d5029b": {"__data__": {"id_": "